main event: A military personnel and a state agent reported sightings of unidentified flying objects in Alexandria, Louisiana in August 1965.
interesting points: The first sighting on 26 August involved a white-yellow star shaped object that exhibited brightening and dimming effects., A state agent's vehicle was struck by a bright object emitting a blue-green light, causing damage to his windshield., Military personnel from Keesler Air Force Base reported seeing a circular object with blue-green lights moving at high speed., The sightings were labeled as reliable observations by the state agent., None of the witnesses had a camera available to document the sightings.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects including a star-shaped and circular object with lights
